{
  "text": "Differences in cytokines levels can be observed in accordance with the applied methodology. Analysis of the IL-6 levels in gingival crevicular fluid (GCF) of patients with CP showed a decrease in disease sites, as compared to non-diseased sites [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, an increase in IL-6 levels could be identified in the gingival connective tissue adjacent to the intra-bony pocket [CITATION_3] and the GCF of sites with CP [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . The present study's data showed no significant differences in IL-4 and IL-6 but did register a significant increase in TNF-a, IL-2, INF-, IL-10, and IL-17 levels in tissues with CP when compared to the NM. By contrast, IL-4 [CITATION_7] and IFN- [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] levels showed a significant reduction in patients with CP, as compared to those of healthy gingival samples, while other studies demonstrated an increase in IL-4 [CITATION_10] and IL-6 [CITATION_11] after treatment, suggesting a protective role for these cytokines.",
